<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Smikkey</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I apologize for this post.  When the Aegis came out and I heard it was a shield, I figured no involved quest was worth 1 wisdom point over the CGS I already had.  Now that I know its a back item, I want one.  <P>Ive searched the site and find pieces of the quest, but nothing complete.  Im sure its here somewhere but I cant find it.  Could someone please help me with some spoiler information??  (Or alot of spoiler info)<P>I get a couple of tells a week in game since Im never anon and 50th level, and Ill pass on the info as well.<P>Thanks In Advance, and good luck to my fellow clerics,<P>Smikkey Giantmaster<BR>50th Level Cleric<BR>Quellious</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Luminar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">heres some info... its broke...<P>unless you want to spend insane amounts of time doing faction quest.. wait 2 weeks for the faction requirments to be fixed.<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Pantheus</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Heh... 2 weeks...<P>/em has a flashback to a movie called The Money Pit. Anytime the contractor was asked how much longer it will take to finish the house, his answer was always "two weeks"... even months later.<P>I suspect they'll be too busy putting fingers in the holes of the RoK dike to be doing any fixing of anything.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">SeaOfHoles</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Agreed.  2 Weeks?  It took them 4 months to fix the Cleric armor AC.  I would be suprised, happy, but suprised if this happened in 2 weeks.<P>------------------<BR><B>Murrachan Moorsfang</B>(44th Rank Dwarven Priest)<BR><B>Briathrachan Moorsfang</B>(36th Rank Halfling Warrior)<BR>Order Of The Red Claw/Mist Riders<BR>Mithaniel Marr</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aldur</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Ok there are 2 parts to the quest<P>1: Items need for quest<BR>2: Faction<P>1. You need a no drop heart and no drop scythe off lord grimrot who resides at the newbie undead camp near to the stone bridge in south karana.  There are two versions of grimrot and two corresponding quest items.  The no drop scythe is off the live version and the no drop heart is off the dead version.  The approximate lvl of the dead version is 25 and the approximate lvl of the live version is 36.<P>Thee is one putrid skeleton that stands (as opposed to siting like the rest) I believe this is the placeholder (although in fits of pure boredom you might just clear the entire lot).  It has been theorized that asking for the quest in qeynos triggers the spawn but noone has been able to verify this.<P>The live version is extremely resistant to magic so best idea is to have a pet tank about to kill him.  If ya lvl 50 and want to try ya luck go ahead but a lvl 35-40 tank or 2 will make short work of grimrot (with a bit of healing).<P>(NOTE: Look at faction section)<P>Ok take said no drop scythe and no drop heart to camlend serbold in qeynos flying saucer (sorry temple of life).  Give him the scythe if he says something strange but not directly bad (took me a while to figure out if he was giving me the finger or not) then give him the heart and woop with joy when you get shield.<P>2. Faction<P>Ok there are a number of ways of increasing faction with the temple of life assuming you are not kos (if you are then ya in trouble).  <P>Bonechips to lashun novashine - waste of time<BR>Money to lashun novashine - waste of time<BR>diseased bear and wolf pelts to priestess caulria - not bad but very difficult to get lots<BR>bandit sashes to Chesgard Sydwen - very good faction not bad loot either.<BR>Koalindl fish to enic ruklin - absolutely amazing faction not bad exp ok coin.<P>Trick to koalindl fishes is to get a lvl 1 to kill them and then let you loot their corpses.  Approximately 50% have a corpse you can hand in.<P>Wolf Form - used for finishing quest.  Not required for all but it doesn't hurt.  Unless you have a gm who can give you back your scythe get it before handing anything in.<P>Remember the key words are "I defend life" to camlend serbold.  I believe I did approximately 13 fishes after getting the quest and I managed to get it (being a dwarf).<P>Hope this helps<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kruass</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Only took me 4 fishes after getting the quest to get my aegis - I wonder if dwarves have a higher faction requirement to get the quest and turn it in.<P>Fishes rule!  What I used was money to Lashun Novashine (35-40pp, 2gp at a time) to get myself to amiable (must be amiable to turn in fishes to Enic), then I turned in about 20 or so fish.  Just hail Cameland and say "I defend life" and he'll either say that the quest only goes to the most trusted members, or he'll tell you about lord grimrot.<P>You'll know you have enough faction to actually get the aegis when you turn in the NO DROP scythe to him and he says "We need the weapon of Lord Grimrot, Pestilence, and his blackened heart to prove your worth."  If he gives you more feed about only the most trusted blah blah blah, then you need to turn in more fish.<P>------------------<BR>Kruass, Cleric, Povar.<p>[This message has been edited by Kruass (edited 04-16-2000).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kronas</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Just wanted to say that I finished the quest today and althogh it is tough it is doable. I am a 35lvl Hafling Cleric on Mith Mar and I have spent the last week working on it. But it was worth the trouble.<P>Good luck!</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Smikkey</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Thank you very much for the info.  I agree that although the faction portion of the quest might me hard, it is merely time consuming, and isnt broken.<P>Can anyone tell me where the Koalindl fish come from??<P>Thanks Smikkey</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Alliliel</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Koalindl fish swim around in the pool under the UFO in the Temple of Life.<P>------------------<BR>Alliliel Archfalcon<BR>Cleric of Tunare<BR>Consul of Initiates<BR>The Sisters of Virtue<BR>Tunare Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Goku</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Where can I find the guy to turn in the fish?       <BR>Is doing the fish quest much better than bandit sashes? I spent 8 hrs at the farm/bandit camp in WK and only got 25 sashes. Is there a better place to get sashes or better quest to build factions. I turned in 500 bone chips, 25 sashes, and 1000 gp to finally get the quest.<P>High elf cleric of RZ</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aldur</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">The guy enic ruklin  is the big strapping knight who is swimming in the pool under the saucer.  He's the one who wollops ya mule alot :><P>Faction wise its incredible.  You will get the same faction from 1 fish that you would from 100's p lots of sashes...simply put do fishes for an hour or so and you will be sorted.  Yes it is a hassle but I camped bandits for a week and got more faction in an hour or 2 of doing fishes than I did handing in 60 sashes.... <P>Save yaself some time and do it the easy way.  If you really want to do the roleplaying version and get the fish from frostbite (the dog for the langsaux quest at barbarian village in west karana (south from the qhills zone)) then you can but remember it is lore no drop....and thats alot of zoning.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kenobe</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Sorry I put all my points in to wisdom so Im a bit slow, so it is posible to get the quest but not have enough faction to complete it, cause although he may give it to you he will not find you worthy after you give him the scythe?<P>Also how did you kill the fish? did you make a newbie and give yourself consent, log off, grab it turn it in and repeat?  <BR>Or did you get a friend to make a newbie, buff him have him kill fish for you?<P>Thank you very much for all you help.<P>------------------<BR>Kenobe Wan<BR>30th Human Cleric<BR>&lt;Praxium&gt;<BR>Cazic-Thule</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
